not shutting you out. Her brain has been chemically reorganised. Here's what you need to know.\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-6 flex items-center gap-3\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-[#d4af37]/20 border border-[#d4af37]/30 flex items-center justify-center\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm font-bold text-[#d4af37] font-serif\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"H\\\"}]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm font-semibold text-white font-sans\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Hakeem Lesolang\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xs text-[#718096] font-sans\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Hypnotherapist \\u0026 Peak Performance Coach\\\"}]]}]]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"w-16 h-px bg-[#d4af37]/30 mb-12\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"prose-custom\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Nobody prepared you for this. The books talked about sleep schedules and nappy brands. Feeding routines and car seat installations. Nobody told you that the woman you love might disappear for a while — not because she wants to, but because her neurochemistry has been fundamentally altered by the single most demanding biological event the human body can undergo.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"2\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"And nobody told you what to do when it happens. Nobody told you how to be the man she needs when she can't tell you what she needs. Nobody told you that your own mental health is on the line too.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"4\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"So let me tell you.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"6\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"What's Actually Happening in Her Brain\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"8\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Postpartum depression (PPD) and postpartum anxiety (PPA) are not weakness. They are not a failure of motherhood. They are neurobiological events with identifiable mechanisms, and understanding those mechanisms is the first thing that will make you useful instead of helpless.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"10\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"During pregnancy, oestrogen and progesterone levels rise to concentrations 10 to 100 times their normal levels. These hormones regulate serotonin, dopamine, and GABA — the neurotransmitters responsible for mood stability, motivation, and calm. After delivery, these hormone levels plummet within 48 hours. The neurochemical floor drops out.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"12\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Simultaneously, the hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal (HPA) axis — the body's central stress-response system — has been recalibrated by pregnancy. Cortisol levels, which were elevated throughout pregnancy to support foetal development, crash and then dysregulate. The result is a stress-response system that is simultaneously exhausted and hypervigilant.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"14\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Add to this: sleep deprivation (which alone can produce psychotic symptoms in clinical studies), the inflammatory response of tissue recovery, possible birth trauma, breastfeeding challenges that further alter prolactin and oxytocin cycling, and the complete reorganisation of identity that motherhood demands.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"16\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"This is not \\\\\\\"baby blues.\\\\\\\" This is a neurobiological storm. And the woman in the middle of it needs you to understand that before anything else.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"18\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Signs You Need to Recognise\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"20\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"PPD doesn't always look like sadness. That's the first mistake most men make — they're watching for crying, for obvious depression, for the Hollywood version of a woman staring out a rain-streaked window.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"22\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Here's what it actually looks like:\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"24\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eIrritability and rage.\\u003c/strong\\u003e She snaps at everything. The way you load the dishwasher. The sound of your breathing. The fact that you asked \\\\\\\"what's for dinner.\\\\\\\" This isn't about the dishwasher. Her amygdala is on a hair trigger because her regulatory neurochemistry is depleted. She has less capacity to modulate emotional responses — not less love for you.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"26\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eWithdrawal and numbness.\\u003c/strong\\u003e She's going through the motions but she's not there. She holds the baby but says she doesn't feel bonded. She looks at you and feels nothing. This is dorsal vagal shutdown — the nervous system's last-resort protection against overwhelm. She hasn't stopped loving you or the baby. Her nervous system has pulled the emergency brake.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"28\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eHypervigilance and intrusive thoughts.\\u003c/strong\\u003e She can't sleep even when the baby sleeps. She checks the baby's breathing seventeen times a night. She has vivid, horrifying intrusive thoughts about harm coming to the baby — and she's terrified that having these thoughts means she's a danger. She's not. Intrusive thoughts in PPA are the brain's threat-detection system in overdrive, not indicators of intent. But she doesn't know that, and the shame is eating her alive.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"30\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003ePhysical symptoms.\\u003c/strong\\u003e Heart racing. Chest tightness. Nausea. Dizziness. Inability to eat. These are autonomic nervous system manifestations of anxiety that are often dismissed as \\\\\\\"just stress\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"adjusting to motherhood.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"32\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eDisconnection from identity.\\u003c/strong\\u003e She doesn't recognise herself. The things she used to enjoy feel alien. She feels like a machine performing functions — feed, change, soothe, repeat — with no access to the person she was before. This is not ingratitude. This is grief. The loss of the pre-motherhood self is real, and it needs to be mourned before the new self can integrate.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"34\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"What She Needs From You (Not What You Think)\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"36\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Your instinct is to fix it. I know. You're a man, you love her, and something is wrong, so you want to identify the problem and solve it. That instinct is honourable. And right now, it's mostly useless.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"38\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Here's what she actually needs:\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"40\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e1. Presence without agenda.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"42\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Sit with her. Not to talk about it. Not to suggest solutions. Not to cheer her up. Just to be a regulated nervous system in the room. Porges' research on co-regulation shows that a calm, grounded person can literally shift the autonomic state of a dysregulated person through proximity alone. Your regulated presence is medicine. Use it.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"44\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\\\\\\"I'm here. You don't have to talk. You don't have to be okay. I'm just here.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"46\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"That sentence, delivered from a genuinely regulated state, is worth more than a hundred suggestions.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"48\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e2. Take tasks without being asked.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"50\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Do not say \\\\\\\"how can I help?\\\\\\\" She doesn't have the executive function to delegate right now. Her prefrontal cortex is running on fumes. Instead, just do things. Feed the baby. Clean the kitchen. Handle the in-laws. Cancel the visitors she doesn't have energy for. Make decisions she doesn't have to make.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"52\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Every task you remove from her plate is cognitive load you're absorbing so her depleted nervous system can direct its limited resources toward recovery.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"54\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e3. Protect her sleep.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"56\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"This is not optional and it is not negotiable. Sleep deprivation is the single most potent accelerant of postpartum mental health deterioration. If she is breastfeeding, work out a system — she pumps, you do one night feed. Or you bring the baby to her, handle the burping and settling, and she goes back to sleep immediately. Do whatever it takes to get her consolidated blocks of 4+ hours. This is neurological triage.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"58\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e4. Normalise professional help.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"60\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"If she is showing signs of PPD or PPA, she needs professional support. Not eventually. Now. A perinatal mental health specialist, medication evaluation if appropriate, and therapeutic support.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"62\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Your role: remove the barriers. Research the providers. Make the appointment. Drive her there. Watch the baby while she's in session. Do not frame it as \\\\\\\"maybe you should talk to someone.\\\\\\\" Frame it as: \\\\\\\"I've found someone who specialises in exactly this. Your appointment is Thursday at 2. I've got the baby.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"64\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e5. Validate without minimising.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"66\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Do not say: \\\\\\\"But look at our beautiful baby.\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\"Other women manage.\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\"You just need to get out of the house.\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\"It'll pass.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"68\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Do say: \\\\\\\"This is real. What you're going through is hard. You're not failing. Your brain is going through something enormous, and I'm not going anywhere.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"70\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"What Nobody Tells You: Your Mental Health Matters Too\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"72\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Here's the part that gets almost zero airtime: \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003epaternal postpartum depression is real, it affects roughly 1 in 10 new fathers, and it is criminally underdiagnosed.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"74\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"The research — led by Dr. James Paulson and others — shows that new fathers experience hormonal shifts too. Testosterone drops. Cortisol and vasopressin fluctuate. Sleep deprivation hits you just as hard neurologically. And the psychological weight of suddenly being responsible for a tiny, fragile human while watching the woman you love struggle — that is not nothing.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"76\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"You may feel:\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"81\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"- Helpless and inadequate. She's suffering and you can't fix it.\\u003cbr /\\u003e- Resentful and guilty for feeling resentful. The baby changed everything and you miss your old life, and you hate yourself for even thinking that.\\u003cbr /\\u003e- Disconnected from the baby. Bonding doesn't always happen instantly for fathers, and the cultural narrative that you should feel overwhelming love from day one can make normal adjustment feel like failure.\\u003cbr /\\u003e- Isolated. Your friends don't want to hear about it. Your family tells you to \\\\\\\"man up.\\\\\\\" There is no infrastructure for struggling new fathers.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"83\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eYour feelings are valid. And they need attention.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"85\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Not at the expense of your partner's needs — she is in the neurobiological crisis and she is the priority for clinical intervention. But you cannot pour from an empty cup, and a dysregulated father cannot co-regulate a dysregulated mother.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"87\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Find your own support. A therapist. A men's group. A friend who won't judge. And if you're in South Africa, know that paternal mental health resources are growing — reach out, ask, insist.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"89\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Neuroscience of the Father's Role in Recovery\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"91\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Your presence in her recovery is not peripheral — it is central. Research by Dr. Ruth Feldman shows that partner support is one of the strongest predictors of PPD recovery speed. The mechanism is neurological: a supportive partner provides consistent co-regulation, which helps stabilise the dysregulated HPA axis. A critical or absent partner does the opposite — amplifying the stress response and prolonging the depressive episode.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"93\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Every time you respond to her distress with patience instead of frustration, you are providing a corrective signal to her nervous system: \\\\\\\"You are not alone in this. The bond is intact. You are safe.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"95\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Every time you respond with irritation, withdrawal, or \\\\\\\"snap out of it,\\\\\\\" you are confirming her deepest postpartum fear: \\\\\\\"I am alone. I am failing. Even my partner can't handle this.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"97\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"The stakes are real. Your behaviour is literally shaping her neurochemical recovery. That is not pressure — that is purpose. You have a role here that nobody else can fill.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"99\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"When to Sound the Alarm\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"101\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Get emergency help immediately if she:\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"107\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"- Expresses thoughts of harming herself or the baby\\u003cbr /\\u003e- Describes hearing voices or seeing things that aren't there\\u003cbr /\\u003e- Seems detached from reality or confused about where she is\\u003cbr /\\u003e- Stops eating, drinking, or sleeping entirely for extended periods\\u003cbr /\\u003e- Says the baby or family would be \\\\\\\"better off without her\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"109\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Postpartum psychosis affects roughly 1-2 per 1,000 births and is a psychiatric emergency. Do not wait. Do not try to handle it alone. Call her healthcare provider or take her to the emergency room.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"111\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Long View\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"113\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Postpartum depression and anxiety are treatable. With appropriate support — professional, pharmaceutical if needed, and relational — the vast majority of women recover fully. But \\\\\\\"fully\\\\\\\" doesn't mean \\\\\\\"quickly\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"easily.\\\\\\\" Recovery is nonlinear. There will be good days and terrible days and days that are both.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"115\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Your job through all of it is the same: be steady. Be present. Be patient. Be the man who says, through his actions, every single day: \\\\\\\"I chose this family. I chose you. And I will keep choosing you through the hardest season of our lives.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"117\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"That is not romance. That is the deepest form of love there is — the kind that shows up when showing up costs you something. The kind that holds the space for her to fall apart so she can put herself back together.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"119\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"You were not prepared for this. Nobody is. But you are here now, reading this, trying to understand. And that already makes you the kind of man she needs.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"121\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Now go be that man. Not perfectly. Just consistently.\\\"}}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L16\\\",null,{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Navigating Postpartum Depression \\u0026 Anxiety: A Guide for Men\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"navigating-postpartum-depression-and-anxiety-a-guide-for-men\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L17\\\",null,{}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-16 rounded-2xl border border-[#d4af37]/30 bg-gradient-to-b from-[#d4af37]/10 to-transparent p-8 text-center\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h3\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xl font-bold text-white font-serif\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Ready to talk about what you just read?\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-2 text-sm text-[#a0aec0] font-sans max-w-md mx-auto\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Book a free discovery call with Hakeem Les